SA
FEDERATION of Trade Union’s general secretary Zwekinzima Vavi has announced
that he and his wife have tested negative for the coronavirus. Vavi took
to Twitter on Thursday to make the announcement. Ï am a
living testimony that the coronavirus can be defeated if we act accordingly to
the regulations that were published,” Vavi said. He said he tested negative yesterday, together
with his wife.  “I want to
thank everybody that sent messages of support to me and the family, those
messages made a huge difference in strengthening our resolve to fight and to
survive,” he added. 